# Scalability

## Definition

Scalability is the ability of an architecture to grow without extensive redesign.

---

## Why It Matters

Requirements change.

A scalable architecture allows:

- New features
- Additional devices
- New communication interfaces
- Product variants

without impacting existing functionality.

---

## Design Techniques Covered

- Publish-Subscribe
- Plugin Architecture
- Event Bus
- Modular Design

